description:
Johnny Concho (1956 - USA)

Western

starring . . . . Frank Sinatra, Keenan Wynn, William Conrad, Wallace Ford
 
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0049384/


The people of Cripple Creek fear Johnny Concho, but only because his brother is a notorious gunfighter. Johnny takes advantage of his position, bullying the townsfolk, until the arrival of a cowboy named Tallman. Tallman claims to have killed Johnny's brother and, after exposing Johnny as a coward, takes over the town. This was Frank Sinatra's first Western and the role allowed him to play against type in his portrayal of the film's villain.
